parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission system can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, or shift gears unexpectedly, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls in traffic
the transmission slips or hesitates
the vehicle won't shift into gear
the transmission warning light illuminates
and the vehicle loses power while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, or experience intermittent electrical issues, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle shuts off while driving
the battery drains suddenly
the electrical system malfunctions
and the vehicle's accessories (e.g.
radio
lights) turn on and off randomly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the blind spot detection system can cause the driver to be unaware of vehicles in the blind spot, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The blind spot warning system malfunctions
the radar module corrodes
and the system fails to detect vehicles in the blind spot.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electronic parking brake can cause the vehicle to unexpectedly brake or lose control, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The parking brake activates while driving
the vehicle slides to a stop
and the parking brake warning light illuminates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition system can cause the vehicle to stall or shut off while driving, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle shuts off while driving
the ignition switch malfunctions
and the key fob or ignition button is easily accidentally activated.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly lurches like it's downshifting
the transmission does not shift
the tachometer reading is too high
the vehicle cannot accelerate above 60mph
the Malfunction Indicator Lamp icon is on
the Brake System Warning light is on
the "Service Power Steering" message appears on the center message board
the "Service Stabili Trak" message appears on the center message board
the "Service Parking Assist" message appears on the center message board.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the shift knob or button can cause the vehicle to become stuck in gear, making it difficult or impossible to shift, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The shift knob or button fractures and detaches
the vehicle is stuck in drive
the vehicle cannot shift into park
the release button on the automatic stick shift pops out
the vehicle will only stay in drive.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the keyless ignition system can cause the engine to shut off unexpectedly, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine shuts off unexpectedly
the tachometer falls to zero
the A/C turns off
the vehicle cannot be restarted in traffic.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can lead to the non-deployment of airbags in the event of a crash, which can result in serious injury or death.
symptoms: The airbag warning light illuminates
the passenger airbag displays "off" when a passenger is present
the passenger airbag displays "on" with a seatbelt warning when no passenger is present
the airbag icon appears on the dashboard
and the service airbag warning appears on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission slipping can cause loss of vehicle control, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: The transmission slips
causing the vehicle to jerk or hesitate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake pedal can cause the vehicle to accelerate unexpectedly, leading to accidents.
symptoms: The brake pedal fails to respond
causing the vehicle to accelerate independently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to shut down while driving, leading to a loss of power steering, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The power steering indicator light comes on
the vehicle shuts down while driving
the power steering loses electrical boost
the radio screen goes off and then cycles through options
the dashboard indicators flash
the vehicle jerks and loses power while driving uphill
the vehicle can only move in reverse.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the steering wheel to lock or become difficult to turn, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The power steering indicator light comes on
the power steering loses electrical boost
the steering wheel locks or becomes difficult to turn
the vehicle vibrates or wobbles while turning
the vibration can be felt in the driver's seat.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission module can cause the vehicle to lose power and become difficult to drive, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle jerks and loses power while driving uphill
the vehicle can only move in reverse
the transmission module shows possible error codes.
